name: Code & Coffee (Bring Laptop!)
description:
Do you like coding with friends? Like really great coffee? Come out to GDI's Code & Coffee!


Code and CoffeeÂ is an opportunity for you to work on your own projects, continue practicing what you've been learning, and meet others who share your interests. Bring your laptop, your recent projects, and your programming problems and questions.

This is also a great event forÂ first time attendeesÂ who just want to socialize or find out more about coding in general. We're very friendly and would love to have you join us. :)


If you have a project idea and some skills, but havenâ€™t attended a GDI event yet? Want to focus on helping others with their projects?Â You're welcome too!

Don't worry if you don't have a project already started. This could be an opportunity to find one.

As a group, weâ€™ll hold each other accountable for completing our projects, and provide on-going support and feedback.

We know that it can be intimidating to come to a meet-up when you don't know anyone, so please feel free to reach out if you have any questions! : )Â


Feel free to come by for the whole thing or drop in when you have time.

Don't forget to bring your laptop and charger if you have one!


All attendees are expected to abide by theÂ Girl Develop It code of conduct.Â

description:
Location:

Providence Public Library

- Rhode Island Room

1. A laptop is required
2. headphones or earbuds are OPTIONAL

Providence Code Night with the Mayor Presented by IntraCity Geeks.

Send all questions to [masked]

Introduction to Web Development!

#ProvidenceCodeNight
#MayorElorza
#IntraCityGeeks

Mayor Elorza has decided to learn how to code and develop websites, and he is inviting you to come out and learn with him... for free! A laptop and an RSVP request is required. Space is limited to 80 attendees. This group will meet once per month and you will receive a complimentary online web development course. You will learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Jquery, Php, MySQL, Bootstrap, APIâ€™s and more as you code and learn how to develop real websites.

IntraCity Geeks assistants will be on hand to assist , work with you and answer any questions you may have.

Providence Code Night with the Mayor takes place on the Second Monday of Every Month. The first event took place on Monday, May 11th 2015 at the Providence Public Library

150 Empire Street, Providence, RI 02903 in their Rhode Island Room

Requirements: A laptop is required.
